  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode fcb86396), kernel_verified on the first attempt. Extends the domain's `cauchy_two_term`/`cauchy_three_term` (fixed small arities) to the general n-term/Finset case, mirroring `general_amgm`'s prior extension of the AM-GM ladder to arbitrary Finset arity. Found the exact Mathlib lemma (`Finset.sum_mul_sq_le_sq_mul_sq`) via `mathlib_search_declarations` before writing any proof attempt, so this went through in a single step with no false starts.",
